         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot Garden ¶ 15/2/72 ¶  ¶ I am just informed, dear Mr Bentham, that the money (£100 –)  ¶ is ¶  available for you, whenever you may call at the Office of the Agent General so Mr Verdon write...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.02.15</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew Correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81, f. 33.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne bot Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">15/2/72</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am just informed, dear Mr Bentham, that the money (£100 –) <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">is</hi>
               </seg> available for you, whenever you may call at the Office of the Agent General so Mr Verdon writes.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Always your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your letter of Christmas day just arrives.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">G. Bentham to M, 25 December 1871.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>What a splendid contribution to science the new vol. of <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">genera</hi>
               </seg> will be!<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83), vol. 2.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am glad you have the 6th vol of the flora in your masterhands.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will despatch shortly the rest of the <name key="Monochlamydeae">Monochlamydeae</name> (Suppl.)</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Pray tell me, whether you want the Orchideae.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>May your health continue good.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>After writing I got from the wreck of the Rangoon your letter of 24 Sept still readable though for days or weeks at the bottom of the sea!<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">G. Bentham to M, 24 September 1871. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Rangoon</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>struck a rock while leaving Galle Harbour on 1 November 1871 (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 27 November 1871, p. 5). The<seg style=""> ink of this letter is now much more faded than that of Bentham’s other letters to M.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I know your wishes for <name key="Monocotyledoneae">Monocotyledoneae</name> now and will attend to them. If you desire really Palms (as mentioned) then they are with Wendland.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See H. Wendland &amp; Drude (1875). See also G. Bentham to M, 15 November 1876, and G. Bentham to M, 30 April 1877. </p>
               </note> But they cannot be placed remote from <name key="Junceae">Junceae</name> and <name key="Xerotideae">Xerotideae</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Monochlamydeae">Monochlamydeae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Monocotyledoneae">Monocotyledoneae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Junceae">Junceae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Xerotideae">Xerotideae</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
